{
  "doc_id": "10109",
  "text": "Associations between potential determinants and individuals' answers were estimated using odds ratios (OR) and the corresponding 95% confidence intervals (95% CI). Stratified analysis was used to control for the effect of each of the potential confounders and, when appropriate, Mantel-Haenszel overall and linear x 2 -tests for associations were used. [CITATION_1] The frequency of the responses varied because of some missing or non-valid answers, and because in some cases more than one answer was possible.",
